  <static seed="56" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring145.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{35x^{5}y^{4}z^{10}-35x^{4}y^{4}z^{9}+25x^{3}y^{4}z^{8}}=</m> <fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5x^{3}y^{4}z^{8}\mathopen{}\left(7x^{2}z^{2}-7xz+5\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>5x^3y^{4}z^{8}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{35x^{5}y^{4}z^{10}-35x^{4}y^{4}z^{9}+25x^{3}y^{4}z^{8}}={5x^{3}y^{4}z^{8}\mathopen{}\left(7x^{2}z^{2}-7xz+5\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
